---
title: interpolate_polynomialcoeff (fulu-polynomial-commitments-sampling)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_assert : assert len(xs) == len(ys)
    q_assert --> q_init_r : r = PolynomialCoeff([0])
    q_init_r --> q_outer : for i in range(len(xs))
    q_outer --> q_summand : summand = PolynomialCoeff([ys[i]])
    q_summand --> q_inner : for j in range(len(ys)), j != i
    q_inner --> q_weight : weight_adjustment = (xs[i] - xs[j]).inverse()
    q_weight --> q_multiply : summand = multiply(summand, [-w*xs[j], w])
    q_multiply --> q_inner : next j
    q_inner --> q_accumulate : r = add_polynomialcoeff(r, summand)
    q_accumulate --> q_outer : next i
    q_outer --> q_return : all i processed
    q_return --> [*] : return r

    note right of q_outer
        INV: All xs values must be distinct (for invertibility)
        INV: Result polynomial has degree at most len(xs) - 1
        INV: evaluate(result, xs[i]) == ys[i] for all i
    end note
